          <span class="bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">Webhooks</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 m-0">Stripe Webhook Receiver</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1 mb-0">
          Point Stripe at your Runlater endpoint. Every event is stored, forwarded to your app with retries, and replayable.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="px-5 py-4 bg-slate-50 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-3">
        <p class="m-0">
          <strong>1.</strong> Create an endpoint in the dashboard with your forward URL(s):
        </p>
        <code class="block bg-slate-900 text-slate-100 rounded-lg p-3 text-xs font-mono">
          https://myapp.com/api/stripe/process
        </code>
        <p class="m-0">
          <strong>2.</strong> Copy the inbound URL and paste it in Stripe's webhook settings:
        </p>
        <code class="block bg-slate-900 text-slate-100 rounded-lg p-3 text-xs font-mono">
          https://runlater.eu/in/ep_abc123...
        </code>
        <p class="m-0">
          <strong>3.</strong>
